columns.name: name
columns.description: The friendly name that identifies the flow log.

columns.name: id
columns.description: Contains ID to identify a flow log uniquely.

columns.name: enabled
columns.description: Indicates whether the flow log is enabled, or not.

columns.name: network_watcher_name
columns.description: The friendly name that identifies the network watcher.

columns.name: provisioning_state
columns.description: The provisioning state of the flow log.

columns.name: type
columns.description: The resource type of the flow log.

columns.name: version
columns.description: The version (revision) of the flow log.

columns.name: etag
columns.description: An unique read-only string that changes whenever the resource is updated.

columns.name: file_type
columns.description: The file type of flow log. Possible values include: 'JSON'.

columns.name: retention_policy_days
columns.description: Specifies the number of days to retain flow log records.

columns.name: retention_policy_enabled
columns.description: Indicates whether flow log retention is enabled, or not.

columns.name: storage_id
columns.description: The ID of the storage account which is used to store the flow log.

columns.name: target_resource_id
columns.description: The ID of network security group to which flow log will be applied.

columns.name: target_resource_guid
columns.description: The Guid of network security group to which flow log will be applied.

columns.name: traffic_analytics
columns.description: Defines the configuration of flow log traffic analytics.
